name: Mote Park Community Orchard
short_description: Heritage fruit in the heart of the park.
description: A community-managed orchard area near the main lake featuring Kentish Cobnuts, apples, and pears.

name: River Medway Wild Garlic
description: The wooded, damp banks along the Medway Towpath (heading toward Allington) are prolific for wild garlic.

name: Incredible Edible Maidstone - Town Centre
description: Street-side planters managed by community groups featuring rosemary, thyme, and seasonal greens.

name: Vinters Valley Sweet Chestnuts
description: The nature reserve is home to several mature sweet chestnut trees and hazel thickets.

name: Barming Wild Plums
short_description: Feral plum trees in the lanes.
description: The quiet lanes and public footpaths in the Barming area often feature wild bullace and plum trees.

name: Medway Valley Blackberries
description: Miles of blackberry bushes line the river path heading north toward Aylesford.

name: Whatman Park Elder
description: Abundant elder bushes for flowers and berries grow along the wilder edges of the park.

name: Otham Walnuts
description: Public footpaths bordering old farm estates in Otham feature several mature walnut trees.

name: Bearsted Green Sloes
description: The hedgerows bordering the green and the railway line are reliable for sloe picking.

name: Len Valley Nature Reserve Wild Mint
description: The damp areas along the River Len are excellent for gathering wild watermint and sorrel.

name: Medway Estuary Samphire (Lower Medway)
description: Though a drive from Maidstone, the salt marshes here offer marsh samphire (check tide times).

name: Coxheath Community Orchard
description: A mix of fruit trees planted for the community, including apples and cherries.

name: White Horse Wood Rosehips
description: Wild rose bushes are common along the edge of the plateau and nature trails.

name: Park Wood Incredible Edible
description: Planters near the community hub and shopping parade featuring chives, mint, and chard.

name: Boxley Road Hazelnuts
description: Hazel trees line the historic paths leading up toward the North Downs Way.
